Ho-hum. I agree that lime juice helped, but the flavor didn't do it for me.

Rating: 4
This is a great recipe, but with one addition - a little lime or lemon juice is a must. Not much salt is needed, but be sure to add at least a little, as it really brings out the flavor.

Rating: 4
Have made many times since recipe came out in 1993. It's chunky with avacados and it's great! I've only served it with tortilla chips but imagine it would work well with other things.

Rating: 4
Everyone I serve this to raves about it. It's wonderful with chips, eggs, burritos - almost anything. I used 3 cloves of garlic and almost twice as much clilantro as the recipe calls for, but everyone may not love cilantro and garlic as much as I do. I will definitely make this again and again.